When we further consider the really spiritual nature of the synagogue services, which were established everywhere for the teaching of the law, and that the psalms of the-period express no sense of a burdensome nature of this applied law, but rather the liveliest delight in its precepts‚ we shall realise what ardour of religion must have inspired this great legal movement.
